    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-10-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="62"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                <head>No. 62.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Logan</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-10-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 3, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 72.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge your No. 122, of the 15th
                    of August last, in regard to the alleged joint action of France, England,
                    Germany and <pb facs="0191" n="121" xml:id="pg_121"/> Italy in the affairs of
                    the Pacific coast of South America, and to approve your refusal to be approached
                    in the matter. Beyond your dispatch the Department as yet has no information on
                    the subject.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
